  <bioghist id="aspace_de43a1d0fa913c108a50a25ecb1350d7">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Reuben Frodin worked as a Program Advisor at the Ford Foundation for over ten years. Most of his time at the Foundation was spent in its International Division. At different times, he was a Program Advisor for Latin America and the Caribbean and Asia and the Pacific. He also had a position in the Division of Education and Research for a short period.</p><p>In addition to his work at the Ford Foundation, Frodin served as the Dean of the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences at the City University of New York (CUNY). He earned his doctorate and law degree from the University of Chicago.</p>  </bioghist>
